(5963, '15', '87', NULL, '15. And remembers (glorifies) the Name \nof his Lord (worships none but Allah), and \nprays (the five compulsory prayers and the\nNawafil — additional prayers).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:08', '2019-11-04 09:40:08'),
(5964, '17', '87', NULL, '17. So give a respite to the disbelievers;\nand leave them for a while.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:08', '2019-11-04 09:40:08'),
(5965, '16', '87', NULL, '16. Nay, you prefer the life of this world, ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:08', '2019-11-04 09:40:08'),
(5966, '18', '87', NULL, '18. Verily, this is in the former Scriptures — ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:08', '2019-11-04 09:40:08'),
(5967, '19', '87', NULL, '19. The Scriptures of Ibrahim (Abraham)\nand Mûsâ (Moses) عليهما السلام', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:08', '2019-11-04 09:40:08'),
(5968, '1', '88', NULL, '1. Has there come to you the narration \nof the overwhelming (i.e. the Day of\nResurrection)?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:08', '2019-11-04 09:40:08'),
(5969, '2', '88', '[1] (V.88:2) It is obligatory to have Belief in the Messengership of the Prophet (Muhammad\nصلى الله عليه وسلم ), Narrated Abu Hurairah رضى الله عنه Allah''s Messenger صلى الله عليه وسلم  said:\n“By Him (Allâh) in Whose Hand Muhammad''s soul is, there is none from amongst the Jews\nand Christians (of these present nations) who hears about me and then dies without\nbelieving in the Message with which | have been sent (i.e. Islâmic Monotheism), but he will\nbe from the dwellers of the (Hell) Fire.” (Sahih Muslim, the Book of Faith, Vol. 1, Hadith\nNo.153-S.S.M.H.20). See also the footnotes of (V.3:85) and (V.41:46).', '2. Some faces, that Day will be humiliated \n(in the Hell-fire, ie. the faces of all\ndisbelievers, Jews and Christians)[1]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:08', '2019-11-04 09:40:08'),
(5970, '3', '88', '[1] (V.88:3) Narrated ‘Abdullah رضى الله عنه “The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم said one statement\nand | said another. The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم said: ‘Whoever dies while still invoking\nanything other than Allah as a rival to Allâh, will enter Hell (Fire).’ And | said, ‘Whoever dies\n\nwithout invoking anything as a rival to Allah, will enter Paradise.”\n\nHadith No. 24).', '3. Labouring (hard in the worldly life by \nworshipping others besides Allah), weary, in\nthe Hereafter with humility and disgrace).[1]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:08', '2019-11-04 09:40:08'),
(5971, '4', '88', NULL, '4. They will enter in the hot blazing Fire.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:08', '2019-11-04 09:40:08'),
(5972, '5', '88', NULL, '5. They will be given to drink from a\nboiling spring,', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:08', '2019-11-04 09:40:08'),
(5973, '6', '88', NULL, '6. No food will there be for them but a\npoisonous thorny plant,', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:08', '2019-11-04 09:40:08'),
(5974, '7', '88', NULL, '7. Which will neither nourish nor avail\nagainst hunger.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:08', '2019-11-04 09:40:08'),
(5975, '8', '88', NULL, '8. (Other) faces that Day will be joyful,', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:08', '2019-11-04 09:40:08'),
(5976, '9', '88', ' [2] (V.88:9) See footnote of (V.18:104).\n(Sahih Al-Bukh4ri, Vol. 6,', '9. Glad with their endeavour (for their\ngood deeds which they did in this world, » along\nwith the true Faith of Islamic Monotheism).[2]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:08', '2019-11-04 09:40:08'),
