(5987, '20', '88', NULL, '20. And at the earth, how it is outspread?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(5988, '21', '88', NULL, '21. So remind them (O Muhammad \nصلى الله عليه وسلم) — you are only one who reminds. ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(5989, '22', '88', NULL, '22. You are not a dictator over them — ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(5990, '23', '88', NULL, '23. Except the one who turns away and\nDisbelieves.[1]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(5991, '24', '88', '[1] (V.88:23) See footnote of (V.8:39).', '24, Then Allah will punish him with the\ngreatest punishment. ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(5992, '25', '88', NULL, '25. Verily, to Us will be their return\n', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(5993, '26', '88', NULL, '26. Then verily, for Us will be their \nreckoning. .', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(5994, '1', '89', NULL, '1. By the dawn', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(5995, '2', '89', NULL, '2. By the ten nights (i.e. the first ten days \nof the month of Dhul-Hijjah),[2]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(5996, '3', '89', '[2] (V.89:2) Narrated Ibn ‘Abbas رضى الله عنهما The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم said, “No good\ndeeds done on other days are superior to those done on these (first ten days of\nDhul-Hijjah).” Then some Companions of the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم  said, “Not even Jihad?”\nHe replied, “Not even Jihad, except that of a man who does it by putting himself and his\nproperty in danger (for Allâh''s sake) and does not return with any of those things.” (Sahih\nAl-Bukhéri, Vol. 2, Hadith No.86).', '3. And by the even and the odd (of all the\ncreations of Allah)[3]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(5997, '4', '89', ' [3] (V.89:3) “Even” and “Odd” is interpreted differently by different religious scholars. Some\nsay: Even is the Day of Slaughtering of the Sacrifices, i.e. 10th of Dhul-Hijjah, and Odd is\nthe Day of ‘Arafah (Hajj), i.e. 9th of Dhul-Hijjah. Others say: Even is all the creatures and\nOdd is Allah. Some say it is the compulsory congregational prayer, i.e. Maghrib is Witr, and\nthe other four prayers are Shaf..', '4, And by the night when it departs.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(5998, '5', '89', NULL, '5. There are indeed in them (the above\noaths) sufficient proofs for men of\nunderstanding (and that, they should avoid all\nkinds of sins and disbeliefs)!', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(5999, '6', '89', NULL, '6. Saw you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم)\nnot how your Lord dealt with ‘Ad (people) -', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6000, '7', '89', NULL, '7. Of Iram (who were very tall) like (lofty) \npillars,', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6001, '8', '89', NULL, '8. The like of which were not created in \nthe land?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6002, '9', '89', NULL, '9. And (with) Thamûd (people), who\nhewed out rocks in the valley (to make\ndwellings)?[1]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6003, '10', '89', NULL, '10. And (with) Fir‘aun (Pharaoh) who had\nthe stakes (to torture men by binding them to\nthe stakes)?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6004, '11', '89', ' [1]. (V.89:9) “And you hew out in the mountains, houses with great skill.” [The Qur''an, Verse\n26:149]', '11. Who did transgress beyond bounds in\nthe lands (in the disobedience of Allâh).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6005, '12', '89', NULL, '12. And made therein much mischief.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6006, '13', '89', NULL, '13. So your Lord poured on them different\nkinds of severe torment.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6007, '14', '89', NULL, '14. Verily, your Lord is Ever Watchful\n(over them).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6008, '15', '89', NULL, '15. As for man, when his Lord tries him\nby giving him honour and bounties, then he\nsays (in exultation): “My Lord has honoured\nme,', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6009, '16', '89', NULL, '16. But when He tries him by straitening\nhis means of life, he says: “My Lord has\nhumiliated me!”', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6010, '17', '89', NULL, '17. Nay! But you treat not the orphans\nwith kindness and generosity (i.e. you neither\ntreat them well, nor give them their exact\nright of inheritance)!', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6011, '18', '89', NULL, '18. And urge not one another on the\nfeeding of Al-Miskin (the needy)!', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6012, '19', '89', NULL, '19. And you devour the inheritance all\nwith greed.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6013, '20', '89', NULL, '20. And you love wealth with much love.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6014, '21', '89', NULL, '21. Nay! When the earth is ground to\npowder. ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6015, '22', '89', NULL, '22. And your Lord comes with the angels \nin rows. ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6016, '23', '89', NULL, '23. And Hell will be brought near that \nDay. On that Day will man remember, but \nhow will that remembrance (then) avail him?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6017, '24', '89', NULL, '24. He will say: “Alas! Would that I had \nsent forth (good deeds) for (this) my life!”', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6018, '25', '89', NULL, '25. So on that Day none will punish as He\nwill punish.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6019, '26', '89', NULL, '26. And none will bind (the wicked, \ndisbelievers and polytheists) as He will bind. .', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6020, '27', '89', NULL, '27. (It will be said to the pious — \nbelievers of Islamic Monotheism): “O (you)\nthe one in (complete) rest and satisfaction!', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6021, '28', '89', NULL, '28.“Come back to your Lord — \nwell-pleased (yourself) and well-pleasing (to\nHim)!', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6022, '29', '89', NULL, '29. “Enter you then among My (honoured)\nslaves, ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6023, '30', '89', NULL, '30. “And enter you My Paradise!”', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6024, '1', '90', NULL, '1. I swear by this city (Makkah); ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6025, '2', '90', NULL, '2. And you are free (from sin, and to \npunish the enemies of Islam on the Day of the\nconquest) in this city (Makkah)''\"[1]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6026, '3', '90', NULL, '3. And by the begetter (i.e. Adam عليه\nالسلام) and that which he begot (i.e. his\nprogeny).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6027, '4', '90', NULL, '4. Verily, We have created man in toil.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6028, '5', '90', NULL, '5. Does he think that none can overcome\nhim?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6029, '6', '90', NULL, '6. He says (boastfully): “I have wasted\nwealth in abundance!”', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6030, '7', '90', NULL, '7. Does he think that none sees him?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6031, '8', '90', NULL, '8. Have We not made for him two eyes,', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6032, '9', '90', NULL, '9. And a tongue and two lips?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6033, '10', '90', NULL, '10. And shown him the two ways (good\nand evil)?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6034, '11', '90', NULL, '11. But he has not attempted to pass on\nthe path that is steep (i.e. the path which will\nlead to goodness and success).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6035, '12', '90', NULL, '12. And what will make you know the\npath that is steep?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6036, '13', '90', '[1](V.90:13) Narrated Abu Hurairah رضى الله عنه ): The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم  said: “Whoever\nfrees a Muslim slave, Allâh will save all the parts of his body from the (Hell) Fire, as he has\nfreed the body-parts of the slave.” (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.3, Hadith No. 693)', '13. (It is) freeing a neck (slave)[1]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6037, '14', '90', NULL, '14. Or giving food in a day of hunger\n(famine),', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6038, '15', '90', NULL, '15. To an orphan near of kin.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6039, '16', '90', NULL, '16. Or to a Miskin (needy) cleaving to\ndust (out of misery).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6040, '17', '90', NULL, '17. Then he became one of those who\nbelieved (in the Islamic Monotheism) and\nrecommended one another to perseverance\nand patience, and (also) recommended one\nanother to pity and compassion.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6041, '18', '90', NULL, '18. They are those on the Right Hand (i.e.\nthe dwellers of Paradise),', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6042, '19', '90', NULL, '19. But those who disbelieved in Our Ayât\n(proofs, evidences, verses, lessons, signs, \nrevelations, etc.), they are those on the Left\nHand (the dwellers of Hell).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6043, '20', '90', ' [1] (V.90:20) “Therein breathing out with deep sighs and roaring will be their portion, and\ntherein they will hear not.**” V.21:100)\n*Ibn Mas‘ûd رضى الله عنه  recited this Verse and then said: “When those (who are destined to\nremain in the Hell-fire forever) will be thrown in the Hell-fire, each of them will be put in a\nseparate Tabût (Box) of Fire, so that he will not see anyone punished in the Hell-fire except\nhe himself.” Then Ibn Mas‘ûd recited this Verse (V.21:100). [Tafsir ibn Kathir, At-Tabar? and\nAl-Qurtubi].', '20. The Fire will be shut over them (i.e.\nthey will be enveloped by the Fire without \nany opening or window or outlet).[1]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6044, '1', '91', NULL, '1. By the sun and its brightness.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6045, '2', '91', NULL, '2. By the moon as it follows it (the sun).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6046, '3', '91', NULL, '3. By the day as it shows up (the sun’s) \nbrightness. ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6047, '4', '91', NULL, '4. By the night as it conceals it (the sun).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6048, '5', '91', NULL, '5. By the heaven and Him Who built it.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6049, '6', '91', NULL, '6. By the earth and Him Who spread it.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6050, '7', '91', NULL, '7. By Nafs (Adam or a person or a soul),\nand Him Who perfected him in proportion;', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6051, '8', '91', NULL, '8. Then He showed him what is wrong for \nhim and what is right for him.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6052, '9', '91', NULL, '9. Indeed he succeeds who purifies his\nownself (i.e. obeys and performs all that\nAllâh ordered, by following the true Faith of\nIslamic Monotheism and by doing righteous\ngood deeds).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6053, '10', '91', NULL, '10. And indeed he fails who corrupts his \nownself (i.e. disobeys what Allah has ordered\nby rejecting the true Faith of Islâmic\nMonotheism or by following polytheism or\nby doing every kind of evil wicked deeds).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6054, '11', '91', NULL, '11. Thamûd (people) denied (their Prophet) \nthrough their transgression (by rejecting the\ntrue Faith of Islâmic Monotheism, and by\nfollowing polytheism, and by committing\nevery kind of sin).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6055, '12', '91', NULL, '12. When the most wicked man among\nthem went forth (to kill the she-camel)', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6056, '13', '91', NULL, '13. But the Messenger of Allah [Salih عليه \nالسلام] said to them: [Be cautious! (Fear the evil\nend)]. That is the she-camel of Allâh! (Do not\nharm it) and (bar it not from having) its drink!”', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6057, '14', '91', NULL, '14, Then they denied him and they killed \nit. So their Lord destroyed them because of\ntheir sin, and made them equal in destruction\n(i.e. all grades of people, rich and poor,\nstrong and weak, etc.)!', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6058, '15', '91', NULL, '15. And He (Allâh) feared not the\nconsequences thereof.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6059, '1', '92', NULL, '1, By the night as it envelops', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6060, '2', '92', NULL, '2. By the day as it appears in brightness. ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6061, '3', '92', NULL, '3. By Him Who created male and female. ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6062, '4', '92', NULL, '4. Certainly, your efforts and deeds are \ndiverse (different in aims and purposes);', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6063, '5', '92', NULL, '5. As for him who gives (in charity) and \nkeeps his duty to Allah and fears Him,', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6064, '6', '92', ' [1] (V.92:6) (A) Al-Husnâ: The Best (i.e. either La ilaha illallah: none has the right to be\nworshipped but Allâh) or a reward from Allâh (i.e. Allâh will compensate him for what he will\nspend in Allâh’s Way or bless him with Paradise).     (B) See the footnote of (V.4:37).', '6. And believes in Al-Husnâ[1]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6065, '7', '92', NULL, '7. We will make smooth for him the path\nof ease (goodness).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6066, '8', '92', ' [1] (V.92:8) Narrated ‘Ali رضى الله عنه, We were in the company of the Prophetصلى الله عليه وسلم \nand he said, \"There is none among you but has his place written for him, either in Paradise\nor in the Hell-fire.” We said, “O Allâh''s Messenger! Shall we depend (on this fact and give\nup work)?” He replied, “No! Carry on doing good deeds, for everybody will find easy (to do)\nsuch deeds as will lead him to his destined place.” Then the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم recited:\n“As for him who gives (in charity) and keeps his duty to Allâh and fear Him, and believes in\nAl-Husnâ. We will make smooth for him the path of ease ... ” (V.92: 5-10)\nAl-Bukhâr, Vol.6, Hadith No.472).', '8. But he who is a greedy miser and\nthinks himself self-sufficient.!\"', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6067, '9', '92', NULL, '9. And denies Al-Husnâ (See the footnote\nof the Verse No. 6).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6068, '10', '92', NULL, '10. We will make smooth for him the path\nfor evil.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6069, '11', '92', NULL, '11. And what will his wealth avail him\nwhen he goes down (in destruction)?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6070, '12', '92', NULL, '12. Truly! On Us is (to give) guidance.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6071, '13', '92', NULL, '13. And truly, to Us (belong) the last\n(Hereafter) and the first (this world).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6072, '14', '92', NULL, '14. Therefore I have warned you of a\nblazing Fire (Hell).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6073, '15', '92', NULL, '15. None shall enter it except the most\nwretched.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6074, '16', '92', NULL, '16. Who denies and turns away.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6075, '17', '92', NULL, '17. And Al-Muttagiin (the pious —- See\nV.2:2) will be far removed from it (Hell).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6076, '18', '92', NULL, '18. He who spends his wealth for increase\nin self-purification,', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6077, '19', '92', NULL, '19. And who has (in mind) no favour\nfrom anyone to be paid back,', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6078, '20', '92', NULL, '20. Except to seek the Countenance of his\nLord, the Most High.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6079, '21', '92', NULL, '21. He surely will be pleased (when he\nwill enter Paradise).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6080, '1', '93', ' [1] (V.93:1): a) Narrated Ibn Abi Laila: Only Umm Hani told us that she had seen the Prophet\nصلى الله عليه وسلم offering the Duhâ (Forenoon prayer). She said.\"On the day of the conquest of\nMakkah, the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم took a bath in my house and offered eight Raka‘at. |\nnever saw him praying such a light prayer but he performed perfect prostrations and\nbowings”. (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.2, Hadith No.207A).\nb) Narrated Abu Hurairah رضى الله عنه My friend (the Prophet) advised me to observe three things:\n(1) to fast three days a month;\n(2) to pray two Raka‘at of Duha prayer (Forenoon prayer); and\n(3) to pray Witr before sleeping.\n(Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.3, Hadith No.202).', '1. By the forenoon (after sunrise).[1]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6081, '2', '93', NULL, '2.By the night when it darkens (and \nstands still).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6082, '3', '93', NULL, '3. Your Lord (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه\nوسلم) has neither forsaken you nor hates you.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6083, '4', '93', NULL, '4. And indeed the Hereafter is better for \nyou than the present (life of this world). ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6084, '5', '93', NULL, '5. And verily, your Lord will give you (all\ngood) so that you shall be well-pleased. ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6085, '6', '93', NULL, '6. Did He not find you (O Muhammad\nصلى الله عليه وسلم) an orphan and gave you a \nrefuge?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6086, '7', '93', NULL, '7. And He found you unaware (of the \nQur’an, its laws and Prophethood) and guided\nyou.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6087, '8', '93', NULL, '8. And He found you poor and made you \nrich (self-sufficient with self-contentment). ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:09', '2019-11-04 09:40:09'),
(6088, '9', '93', NULL, '9. Therefore, treat not the orphan with \noppression. “', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6089, '10', '93', NULL, '10. And repulse not the beggar. ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10');
INSERT INTO `aya_translates_en` (`id`, `aya`, `sura`, `tafser`, `aytext`, `lang`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(6090, '11', '93', NULL, '11. And proclaim the Grace of your Lord \n(i.e. the Prophethood and all other Graces).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6091, '1', '94', '[1] (V.111:1) Narrated Ibn ‘Abbas tis ail.) : “When the Verse, ‘And warn your tribe (O\nMuhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم ) of near kindred.’ (V.26:214) was revealed, Allah’s Messenger\nصلى الله عليه وسلم went out, and when he had ascended As-Safa mountain, he shouted, ‘Ya\nSabahah!* The people said, ‘What is that?’ Then they gathered around him, whereupon he\nsaid, ‘Do you see? If | inform you that cavalrymen are proceeding up the side of this\nmountain, will you believe me?’ They said, ‘We have never heard you telling a lie.’ Then he\nsaid, | am a plain warner to you of a coming severe punishment.’ Abu Lahab said, ‘May you\nperish! You gathered us only for this reason?’ Then Abu Lahab went away. So [Sdrat\nAl-Masad] ‘Perish the hands of Abu Lahab!’ was revealed. (V.111:1). (Sahih Al-Bukhari,\nVol. 6, Hadith No. 495).\n* “Y4 Sabdéhah!” is an Arabic expression used when one appeals for help or draws the\nattention of others to some danger.', '1. Have We not opened your breast for\nyou (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم )?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6092, '2', '94', NULL, '2. And removed from you your burden', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6093, '3', '94', NULL, '3. Which weighed down your back ?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6094, '4', '94', '[2] (V.111:4) ‘And his wife too, who carries wood.’ Mujahid said, ‘Carries the wood’ means\nthat she used to slander (the Prophet als 4ue «i! i.) and goes about with calumnies.', '4. And have We not raised high your fame?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6095, '5', '94', '[3] (V.111:5) “In her neck is a twisted rope of palm fibre, [i.e. the chain which is in the Fire (of\nHell)).” (Sahih Al-Bukh4ri, Vol.6, Chapter 356, Page 469).\n[imam Qurtubi says in the Tafsir of the (V.17:45)]:\nNarrated Sa‘id ibn Jubair رضى الله عنه): “When Sirah No.111 Al-Masad was revealed, the\nwife of Abu Lahab came looking out for the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم while Abu Bakr رضى الله عنه\nwas sitting beside him. Abu Bakr said to the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم ‘| wish if you get\naside (or go away) as she is coming, to us, she may harm you’. The Prophet said: ‘There\nwill be a screen set between me and her’. So she did not see him alsy due ail le. She said\nto Abu Bakr: ‘Your companion is saying poetry against me.’ Abu Bakr said: ‘By Allah he\ndoes not say poetry.’ She said: ‘Do you believe that’. Then she left. Abu Bakr said, ‘O\nAllah''s Messenger! She did not see you’. The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم said: ‘An angel was\nscreening me from her.’”_[ This Hadith is quoted from Musnad Abû ya''la]\nIt is said that if the Verse {(17:45) The Qur''an] is recited by a real believer (of Islamic\nMonotheism) he will be screened from a disbeliever. (Allah knows best). (Tafsir A/-Qurtubi,\nVol.10, Page 269).', '5. Verily, along with every hardship is relief,', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6096, '6', '94', NULL, '6. Verily, along with every hardship is\nrelief (i.e. there is one hardship with two reliefs,\nso one hardship cannot overcome two reliefs).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6097, '7', '94', NULL, '7.So when you have finished (your\noccupation), devote yourself to Allâh’s worship.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6098, '8', '94', NULL, '8. And to your Lord (Alone) turn (all\nyour) intentions and hopes.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6099, '1', '95', NULL, '1. By the fig, and the olive.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6100, '2', '95', NULL, '2. By Mount Sinai.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6101, '3', '95', ' [1] (V. 95:3) See footnote of (V.2:191).', '3. By this city of security (Makkah).[1]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6102, '4', '95', NULL, '4. Verily, We created man in the best\nstature (mould).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6103, '5', '95', NULL, '5. Then We reduced him to the lowest of\nthe low.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6104, '6', '95', NULL, '6. Except those who believe (in Islâmic\nMonotheism) and do righteous deeds. Then\nthey shall have a reward without end (Paradise).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6105, '7', '95', NULL, '7. Then what (or who) causes you (O\ndisbelievers) to deny the Recompense (i.e.\nthe Day of Resurrection)?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6106, '8', '95', NULL, '8.Is not Allâh the Best of judges?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6107, '1', '96', NULL, '1. Read! In the Name of your Lord Who \nhas created (all that exists). ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6108, '2', '96', NULL, '2. He has created man from a clot (a piece \nof thick coagulated blood). ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6109, '3', '96', NULL, '3. Read! And your Lord is the Most \nGenerous.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6110, '4', '96', NULL, '4. Who has taught (the writing) by the pen. ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6111, '5', '96', NULL, '5. He has taught man that which he knew\nnot. ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6112, '6', '96', NULL, '6. Nay! Verily, man does transgress (in\ndisbelief and evil deed). _', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6113, '7', '96', NULL, '7.Because he considers himself \nself-sufficient.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6114, '8', '96', NULL, '8. Surely, to your Lord is the return.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6115, '9', '96', NULL, '9. Have you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه\nوسلم) seen him (i.e. Abu Jahl) who prevents', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6116, '10', '96', NULL, '10. A slave (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم)\nwhen he prays?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6117, '11', '96', NULL, '11, Have you seen if he (Muhammad (صلى \nالله عليه وسلم) is on the guidance (of Allâh)', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6118, '12', '96', NULL, '12. Or enjoins piety?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6119, '13', '96', NULL, '13. Have you seen if he (Abû Jahl) denies\n(the truth, i.e. this Qur’ân) and turns away?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6120, '14', '96', NULL, '14. Knows he not that Allah sees (what he \ndoes)? ', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6121, '15', '96', NULL, '15. Nay! If he (Abû Jahl) ceases not, We\nwill catch him by the forelock —', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6122, '16', '96', NULL, '16. A lying, sinful forelock!', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6123, '17', '96', NULL, '17. Then let him call upon his council (of\nhelpers).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6124, '18', '96', NULL, '18. We will call out the guards of Hell (to\ndeal with him)!', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6125, '19', '96', ' [*] (V.96:19) Prostration (see Appendix 1).', '19. Nay! (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم)!\nDo not obey him (Abû Jahl). Fall prostrate\nand draw near (to Allâh)! [*]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6126, '1', '97', ' [1] (V.97:1)\"Therein (that night) is decreed every matter of ordainments.” (Verse 44:4 )**\n** i.e., the matters of deaths, births, provisions, calamities for the whole (coming) year as\ndecreed by Allah.', '1. Verily, We have sent it (this Our\"ân)\ndown in the night of Al-Qadr (Decree).\"[1]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6127, '2', '97', NULL, '2. And what will make you know what\nthe night of Al-Qadr (Decree) is?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6128, '3', '97', NULL, '3. The night of Al-Qadr (Decree) is better\nthan a thousand months (i.e. worshipping\nAllâh in that night is better than worshipping\nHim a thousand months, i.e. 83 years and 4\nmonths).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6129, '4', '97', NULL, '4. Therein descend the angels and the Rûh\n[Jibril (Gabriel)] by Allâh’s Permission with\nall Decrees,', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6130, '5', '97', ' [2] (V.97:5) Narrated ‘Aishah رضى الله عنها Allah''s Messenger صلى الله عليه وسلم said, “Search for\nthe Night of Qadr in the odd nights of the last ten nights of Ramadan.” (Sahih Al-Bukhari,\nVol 3, Hadith No.234).', '5. (All that night), there is Peace (and\nGoodness from Allâh to His believing slaves)\nuntil the appearance of dawn[2]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6131, '1', '98', ' [1] (V.98:1) Al-Mushrikûn: polytheists, pagans, idolaters and disbelievers in the Oneness of\nAllah and His Messenger Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم', '1. Those who disbelieve from among the \npeople of the Scripture (Jews and Christians) \nand Al-Mushrikûn,[1] were not going to leave\n(their disbelief) until there came to them the\nclear evidence.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6132, '2', '98', NULL, '2. A Messenger (Muhammad صلى الله عليه\nوسلم) from Allah, reciting (the Qur’ân) purified \npages [purified from Al-Baril (falsehood)].', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6133, '3', '98', NULL, '3. Wherein are correct and straight laws\nfrom Allâh.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6134, '4', '98', NULL, '4. And the people of the Scripture (Jews \nand Christians) differed not until after there\ncame to them the clear evidence (i.e. Prophet\nMuhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم and whatever\nwas revealed to him).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6135, '5', '98', NULL, '5. And they were commanded not, but \nthat they should worship Allah, and worship \nnone but Him Alone (abstaining from \nascribing partners to Him), and perform\nAs-Salat (Iqâmat-as-Salât) and give Zakât\nand that is the right religion.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6136, '6', '98', ' [2] (V.98:6) It is obligatory to have Belief in the Messengership of the Prophet (Muhammad\nصلى الله عليه وسلم Narrated Abu Hurairah رضى الله عنه Allah''s Messenger صلى الله عليه وسلم said:\n“By Him (Allah) in Whose Hand Muhammad''s soul is, there is none from amongst the Jews\nand Christians (of these present nations) who hears about me and then dies withoutbelieving in the Message with which | have been sent (i.e. Islâmic Monotheism) but he will\nbe from the dwellers of the (Hell) Fire.” (Sahih Muslim, the Book of Faith, Vol. 1, Hadith No\n153-S.S.M.H.20). See also (V.3:85) and (V.3:116).                  ', '6. Verily, those who disbelieve (in the \nreligion of Islam, the Qur’an and Prophet\nMuhammad buy te ai! ls) from among the\npeople of the Scripture (Jews and Christians)\nand Al-Mushrikin will abide forever in the\nFire of Hell. They are the worst of creatures. [2]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6137, '7', '98', NULL, '7. Verily, those who believe [in the Oneness \nof Allâh, and in His Messenger Muhammad\nصلى الله عليه وسلم) including all obligations \nordered by Islâm] and do righteous good\ndeeds, they are the best of creatures.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6138, '8', '98', NULL, '8. Their reward with their Lord is ‘Adn\n(Eden) Paradise (Gardens of Eternity),\nunderneath which rivers flow. They will\nabide therein forever, Allâh will be pleased\nwith them, and they with Him That is for\nhim who fears his Lord.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6139, '1', '99', NULL, '1. When the earth is shaken with its\n(final) earthquake.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6140, '2', '99', NULL, '2. And when the earth throws out its\nburdens.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6141, '3', '99', NULL, '3. And man will say: ‘““What is the matter\nwith it?”', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6142, '4', '99', NULL, '4. That Day it will declare its information\n(about all that happened over it of good or\nevil).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6143, '5', '99', NULL, '5, Because your Lord will inspire it.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6144, '6', '99', ' [1] (V.99:6) See footnote of (V.11:18).', '6. That Day mankind will proceed in\nseated groups that they may be shown their\ndeeds.[1]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6145, '7', '99', NULL, '7. So whosoever does good equal to the\nweight of an atom (or a small ant) shall see it.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6146, '8', '99', NULL, '8. And whosoever does evil equal to the\nweight of an atom (or a small ant) shall see it.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6147, '1', '100', NULL, '1. By the (steeds) that run, with panting.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6148, '2', '100', NULL, '2. Striking sparks of fire (by their hooves).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6149, '3', '100', NULL, '3. And scouring to the raid at dawn.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6150, '4', '100', NULL, '4, And raise the dust in clouds the while.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6151, '5', '100', NULL, '5. And penetrating forthwith as one into\nthe midst (of the foe).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6152, '6', '100', NULL, '6. Verily, man (disbeliever) is ungrateful\nto his Lord.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6153, '7', '100', NULL, '7. And to that he bears witness (by his deeds).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6154, '8', '100', NULL, '8. And verily, he is violent in the love of\nwealth.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6155, '9', '100', NULL, '9. Knows he not that when the contents of\nthe graves are poured forth (all mankind is\nresurrected)?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6156, '10', '100', NULL, '10. And that which is in the breasts (of\nmen) shall be made known?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6157, '11', '100', NULL, '11. Verily, that Day (i.e. the Day of\nResurrection) their Lord will be\nWell-Acquainted with them (as to their deeds\nand will reward them for their deeds).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6158, '1', '101', NULL, '1. Al-Qari‘ah (the striking Hour i.e. the\nDay of Resurrection).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6159, '2', '101', NULL, '2. What is the striking (Hour)?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6160, '3', '101', NULL, '3. And what will make you know what\nthe striking (Hour) is?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6161, '4', '101', NULL, '4. It is a Day whereon mankind will be\nlike moths scattered about.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6162, '5', '101', NULL, '5. And the mountains will be like carded\nwool.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6163, '6', '101', ' [1].(V.101-6) See footnote of (V.7:8).', '6. Then as for him whose balance (of\ngood deeds) will be heavy, [1]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6164, '7', '101', NULL, '7. He will live a pleasant life (in Paradise).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6165, '8', '101', NULL, '8. But as for him whose balance (of good\ndeeds) will be light,', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6166, '9', '101', NULL, '9. He will have his home in Hâwiyah (pit,\ni.e. Hell).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6167, '10', '101', NULL, '10. And what will make you know what it\nis?', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6168, '11', '101', NULL, '11. (it is) a fiercely blazing Fire!', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6169, '1', '102', NULL, '1. The mutual rivalry (for piling up of\nworldly things) diverts you,', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6170, '2', '102', NULL, '2. Until you visit the graves (i.e. till you\ndie).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6171, '3', '102', NULL, '3. Nay! You shall come to know!', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6172, '4', '102', NULL, '4. Again nay! You shall come to know!', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6173, '5', '102', NULL, '5. Nay! If you knew with sure knowledge\n(the end result of piling up, you would not\nhave been occupied yourselves in worldly\nthings).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6174, '6', '102', NULL, '6. Verily, You shall see the blazing Fire\n(Hell)!', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6175, '7', '102', NULL, '7. And again, you shall see it with certainty\nof sight!', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6176, '8', '102', ' [1] (V.102:8) Narrated Abu Hurairah رضى الله عنه Once during a day or a night, Allâh’s\nMessenger صلى الله عليه وسلم came out and found Abu Bakr and ‘Umar رضى الله عنهما he said:\n“What has brought you out of your homes at this hour?” They replied: “Hunger, O Allâll''s\nMessenger.” He said: “By Him (Allâh) in Whose Hand my soul is, | too have come out for\nthe same reason for which you have come out”. Then he صلى الله عليه وسلم said to them (both):\n“Come along!”And he went along with them to a man from the Ansar but they did not find\nhim in his house. The wife of that man saw the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم and said: “You are\nwelcome.” Allah’s Messenger صلى الله عليه وسلم asked her (saying): “Where is so-and-so?” She\nreplied: “He has gone to fetch some water for us.” In the mean time the Ansar? man came,\nhe saw Allah’s Messenger صلى الله عليه وسلم with his two Companions and said: “All praise and\nthanks are Allâh’s: today there is none superior to me as regards guests.” Then he went and\nbrought a part of a bunch of date-fruit, having dates, some still green, some ripe and some\nfully ripe and requested them to eat from it. He then took his knife (to slaughter for them a\nsheep). Allâh’s Messenger صلى الله عليه وسلم said to him: “Beware! Do not slaughter a milch\nsheep”. So he slaughtered a sheep (prepared the meals from its meat). They ate from that\nsheep and that bunch of dates and drank water. After they had finished eating and drinking\nto their fill, Allâh’s Messenger صلى الله عليه وسلم said to Abu Bakr and ‘Umar رضى الله عنه “By\nHim in Whose Hand my soul is, you will be asked about this treat on the Day of\nResurrection. He (Allâh) brought you out of your homes with hunger and you are not\nreturning to your homes till you have been blessed with this treat.” (Sahih Muslim, Vol.6,\nThe Book of Foods and Drinks, Hadith.No.2038-S.S.M.H.1306).', '8. Then on that Day you shall be asked\nabout the delights[1] (you indulged in, in this -\nworld):', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6177, '1', '103', NULL, '1. By AL- ‘Asr (the time).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6178, '2', '103', NULL, '2. Verily, man is in loss,', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6179, '3', '103', NULL, '3. Except those who believe (in Islâmic \nMonotheism) and do righteous good deeds, \nand recommend one another to the truth [i.e. \norder one another to perform all kinds of\ngood deeds (Al-Ma‘rif) which Allâh has\nordained, and abstain from all kinds of sins\nand evil deeds (Al-Munkar) which Allâh has\nforbidden], and recommend one another to\npatience (for the sufferings, harms, and\ninjuries which one may encounter in Allâh’s\nCause during preaching His religion of\nIslamic Monotheism or Jihâd).', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
