(6199, '2', '107', '[1].(V.107:2) Narrated Sahl ibn Sa''dرضى الله عنهما : The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم said, “I and the\nperson who looks after an orphan and provides for him, will be in Paradise like this,” putting\nhis index and middle fingers together. (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.8, Hadith No.34).', '2. That is he who repulses the orphan \n(harshly), [1]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
(6200, '3', '107', ' [2] (V.107:3) Narrated Abu Hurairah رضى الله عنه The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم said, “The one\nwho looks after a widow or a poor person is like a Mujahid (fighter) who fights for Allah’s\nCause, or like him who performs prayers all the night and fasts all the day.” (Sahih\nAl-Bukh4ri, Vol.7, Hadith No.265).', '3. And urges Hot on the feeding of \nAl-Miskin (the needy), “', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:10', '2019-11-04 09:40:10'),
