(6231, '1', '114', '[1] (V.114:1) Narrated ‘Aishah رضى الله عنها  : Whenever Allah''s Messengerصلى الله عليه وسلم \nwent to bed, he used to recite Sûrat Al-Ikhlas (112), Sûrat Al-Falaq (113) and Sûrat An-Nâs\n(114) and then blow on his palms and pass them over his face and those parts of his body\nthat his hands could reach. And when he fell ill, he used to order me to do like that for him.\n(Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol. 7, Hadith No. 644).', '1. Say: “I seek refuge with (Allâh) the\nLord of mankind,[1]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:11', '2019-11-04 09:40:11'),
(6232, '2', '114', '[2] (V.114:2) The Statement of Allâh عز وجل  ‘The King of mankind.’\nNarrated Abu Hurairah رضى الله عنه The Prophet  صلى الله عليه وسلم  said, “On the Day of\nResurrection Allah will grasp the whole (planet of) earth (by His Hand) and shall roll up the\nheaven with His Right Hand and say, ‘| am the King. Where are the kings of the earth?”\n(Sahih Al-Bukhéri, Vol. 9, Haaith No. 479).', '2. The King of mankind —\"[2]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:11', '2019-11-04 09:40:11'),
