(6234, '4', '114', '[3]. (V.114:4) Narrated Abu Hurairah رضى الله عنه: Allah’s Messenger صلى الله عليه وسلم said, “The\n(Hell) Fire is surrounded by all kinds of desires and passions, while Paradise is surrounded\nby all kinds of disliked undesirable things.”* (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol. 8, Hadith No. 494).\n* Inordinate desires and animalistic passions lead to the Fire while self-control,\nperseverance, chastity and all other virtues, and the obedience to Allah and His Messenger\nصلى الله عليه وسلم lead to Paradise. What leads to Hell is easy to do while what leads to\nParadise is difficult to do.', '4. From the evil of the whisperer (devil\nwho whispers evil in the hearts of men) who\nwithdraws (from his whispering in one’s\nheart after one remembers Allah)[3]', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:11', '2019-11-04 09:40:11'),
(6235, '5', '114', NULL, '5. Who whispers in the breasts of mankind.', 'en', '2019-11-04 09:40:11', '2019-11-04 09:40:11'),
